rComments: Failed in her class once but took it again in the summer when I wasn't crowded with other work and found the class really simple, it may have been because I already took it, but a 40+% improvement from winter to summer shows how when you focus during her lectures, an A really is possible with minimal effort.
Very passionate and professional in her field.
Kathleen's amazing. That's it.
She is genuinely passionate about teaching math

Kathleen is truly a gem of the UTSC math department. Like no other professor she understands the students' needs and expectations. Her lectures are engaging (as engaging as math can ever be) and makes great use of examples. Kathleen is fair and friendly. She makes herself available as much as possible. She gives the test format ahead of time.

Kathleen holds interesting lectures, make sure you go to those. She got hit by a bus and still taught the semester real OG couldn't lift her left shoulder to write on the board. Her assignments prepare you well. Go to lectures do readings finish assignments and you're basically guaranteed a good mark.

Kathleen was one of my favourite profs. She loves what she teaches so her lectures are very interesting and she explains all concepts very thoroughly with many examples. The material itself is difficult sometimes, as are her midterm and final but doing all her assignment AND exercise questions goes a long way.

Kathleen is my favourite prof, she's just amazing! Her lectures are amazing and she explains things clearly. She is always willing to help in office hours, even stays back an extra hour to help. MAKE SURE TO DO ALL HER OPTIONAL EXERCISE QUESTIONS. Her midterm and final are hard but completely doable if you do the exercises and ask for help weekly.

Sitting in her lectures feel like going to a play, extremely enthusiastic about math. Really cares about her students, I handed in a wrong assignment and she went out of her way to set up a make up evaluation. On final and midterm, don't study proofs of big theorems(FTOC, series tests,C.T), do the 'extra' section on the assignments.

She's absolutely the best professor I've had in UTSC. She gives amazing lectures and is always passionate about math. Always willing to help students after class. Even arranged 1-1 meetings for students who didn't do well in midterm and wanted to talk to her about study strategies.

She's just so good at lecturing, definitely one of the best. Learned a lot more compared to A31, worked a lot harder than A31, but got a lot lower than A31 lol. The exams are so f***ing hard and long. The marking scheme is also extremely strict, so definitely be rigorous when doing them.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Lots of homework', 'Tough grader']

rComments: Literally one of the only two courses that I am actively willing to go to( the other one being Anya's CSCA08). She makes lectures super intriguing. It is a bit of pain that there is no weboption but I can't think of a reason you don't go to the class (other than time conflict etc).
Shes great at explaining stuff. Lectures are always interesting.
One of the best professors i've ever head! She's incredibly engaging in lecture. Exams are fair. Attendance is not mandatory, but course can be difficult so attending lecture is a must
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Amazing lectures', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: The best prof I've ever had. Though I'm not the biggest fan of calculus, she somehow got me to enjoy it. She is incredibly caring, so much so that when we entered the exam room, there were chocolate bars next to the exams. She even asked for a class pic. Her criteria is clear. Do your assignments and practice her lec material and you will pass.
enthusiastic about the course explains how to deal with a question clearly her tests are hard but not too difficult if you finish all of the assignments and excercises
detail oriented and respects the opinion of the students

Best prof I've met at UTSC. Although I've transferred to UTSG, I will still take her course if I need. She is really nice and cares her students' success. Hard exams but you will be okay if you keep practicing. Homeworks are helpful. Plz go to her office hour or aks her any question after her lecture, she will always be there for help!
One of the few profs at UTSC that actually cares about her students.

Best professor I've had so far, wish I could have her for every math class. Made calculus so easy to understand. MATA37 was rather difficult due to the amount of content and the little things you lose marks for that add up . You have to work for it. None of the exam questions were harder than the exercises she gives, if you do them you are set.
Amazing lectures, as a Maths Ph.D. she has the real passion for Maths--even for the most basic first-year calculus course.

Shes one of the most amazing professors Ive met in UTSC. I fell in love with her when she told the joke if you guys wanna kill me, you have to kill me 5 business days before your midterm because thats when we need to give the exam to the photocopy guy when she asked a really simple question but no one said anything.

Best professor ever. She's very friendly, approachable, and inspirational. When she's teaching mathematics, it's like she's telling you a story. My role model. I'm looking forward to taking upper year courses with her :D

This woman is a fudging legend. I didn't get anything in mata31 but I understand everything she does. The way she teaches just make your brain SOAK the knowledge, like an industrial sponge. Best Prof at utsc. The course might be hard but she makes it enjoyable, I look forward to her lectures.
Kind, outgoing and willing to help everyone. A prof and a friend.
Best math prof ever. She's hard, but her lectures are SO clear that you understand all hard concepts easily. She also cares about her students very much! AMAZING prof!
The best prof I have had at utsc so far. Explains concepts slowly and clearly and with enthusiasm. Tough course but she will make you like math.
Great prof, hard course.
woooo
She is a great prof, very clear lecture and very helpful outside of class ,  however the exams are very hard

She is absolutely the besttttttt calculus teacher ever. Unfortunately,  I had to re-take Calc part 2. The first time I had Professor Thanhoffer idk his full name tbh but I re-took it and I realized how much i DIDN'T know last year. I learned so much from her and she REALLY makes sure you get the material.  p.s. PRACTICE MAKES PERFECT, so do ur hwk

Kathleen was hands down one of the BEST professors. Absurdly nice, very engaging, funny, and always told you what was on the test/midterm. She was possibly the best math teacher I've ever had. Class was really hard (I didn't study hard enough!), but Kathleen definitely won't be the reason you fail.
she's great in lectures and helping out but her tests are tough and on top of that, she's a tough grader
GREAT PROFESSOR, but course was brutal. Really makes you work hard in order to get the mark that you want.

Kathleen is a very charismatic, and influential lecturer. What she says does have an impact on people. 'If she steps on something, it is palpable'. That is not to say she is to compromise standards, credit only where credit is appropriately due. Just hope she understands that people listen.

Kathleen is a passionate lecturer whose enthusiasm for calculus shows in every lecture. She explains ideas concisely and uses numerous examples to explain her ideas. Completing homework assignments is essential to mastering concepts however and sometimes the lectures don't go as far in depth as the assignments do.
Fantastic lecturer, does a great job teaching! The course is brutal, but I am glad Kathleen Smith was the one that taught it.

She is the most amazing mathematics teacher I've ever seen. She is so passionate about math which makes me fall in love with math more and motivates me to give my 200%. I would definitely recommend everyone to pick her lecture !
She's very passionate about her teaching. gives clear explanations and will make time to help any struggling students.

Kathleen is the best math instructor I have ever had from all my years of studies. She gives very clear explanations and notes are top notch. She clearly loves mathematics and she teaches much better than any prof I had at UTSC. She loves when you ask questions and holds long office hours. She is not even a Professor (PhD student)! She is AMAZING!

No words to describe how amazing she is! Extremely clear when teaching and she goes above and beyond to help out her students with their questions and problems. With that being said, getting a great mark in the course won't be easy (duh, it's calculus), but it's totally do-able. Not only an amazing prof, but a kind person.

AMAZING PROFESSOR!!!!!!! She is probably the best in the world at teaching. She knows so much about math but more importantly, she has tremendous passion to help students. NO other prof is as good as her!!
Very helpful prof but can murder you on the exam.
best professor ever. She is the only math professor to grab my attention.

SHE IS AMAZING! I LOVE LOVE LOVE LOVE(infinity times) HER!!!!! Omgsh.. wow.. too much words to describe :) she is definetly my hero. She helped soo much. I had 8am class with her, and I woke up EXTRA early just for her class and teaching and I got happy when I am in her class even though its calculus :) SHES TOO COOL TO BE TRUE!!! <3 BEST PROF EVER
